he board clock vs my clock.  I attempted last night, prior to trying to post a reservation to try and synchronize my clock with the board clock.  Well, it didn't work.  I posted too early.... by several minutes.  I reposted well after midnight.. figuring I would maybe still have a shot.. even though I knew it wouldn't be 12:00:00 on the nose.  It turns out my second posting was the earliest... and I thought legal.  It turns out that my early post (although invalid due to being more than 2 weeks early) was considered my first post.. therefore rendering my later post no good???  So the first is deleted due to be too early, the second is deleted since it is the second for the same day???? I don't understand how this is fair.  I read the rules.. the very first reads: <br>
<br>
&quot;You cannot post more than 2 weeks ahead of the start of the raid.  Post will be deleted if it breaks the rule.  Board time will be used to determine this&quot;<br>
<br>
  umm ok.. so delete my first.  Then I only have one post... and since it was the earliest... it should get the reservation.. yes?<br>
<br>
The fifth rule reads:<br>
<br>
&quot;Do not post multiple times for the same date.  If more than one person from a guild posts a reservation for a date, only the earlier one will be accepted.  If a person posts multiple times for the same date, all posts beyond the first will be deleted&quot;<br>
<br>
I understand the concept....but if the first rule is enforced.. then my second post becomes my first doesn't it?  I don't see it as necesarily fair that both posts become invalid.  I am only trying to get one legit post in.. cmon?  Does that mean if someone accidently posts an entire month early that they nor anyone in their guild can try and post for that date again??  That doesn't seem to make good sense at all.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Just trying to follow reasonable rules.<br>
<br>
<br>
Syrillian<br>
